post_text: Valley Park School District will now be able to serve free meals to all children 18 and under living in Valley Park School District. Meal distribution is currently taking place Monday, Wednesday, and Friday from 10:30 a.m.-12:00 p.m. in front of the secondary cafeteria. TWIGS will also continue to be on-site every Friday to distribute free food essentials to any family picking up meals. Come on up! #VPpride #VPStrong

Grab-N-Go meal service will be paused Monday, September 7, due to the Labor Day holiday. Grab-N-Go will resume on Wednesday, September 9, with meals for the rest of the week. Meals distributed on Friday September 4 will include enough food for meals for Friday, Monday, and Tuesday. Meal distribution is from 10:30-Noon.

Twigs will also be here Friday to pass out a box of essentials.

Mrs Hardison works with students in 2nd and 5th grade.

post_text:
The Valley Park Board of Education will hold its regularly scheduled August 26th meeting virtually on Facebook Live at 7:15 p.m.

The meeting may be viewed by visiting: https://tinyurl.com/VPBOE0826

The Board of Education welcomes comments from its community on posted agenda items and has established a process for hearing comments from the public during electronic meetings.
Agenda: https://tinyurl.com/vpaugboeagenda

Any person wishing to address the Board during an electronic meeting must fill out this form by 4 p.m. on the date of the meeting: https://tinyurl.com/vp8262020

The form will include the speaker’s name, address, e-mail address, and comments.

Starting August 24th the Valley Park School District will offer curbside breakfast & lunch offerings on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday from 10:30 a.m.-noon.
Meals will include two complete breakfasts and lunches.
Meals will be charged, at pick up time, according to your eligibility status of the Free & Reduced Meal Program or they will be full price.
Meal Prices, Menus, and Free/Reduced Lunch Applications can be found by visiting: https://tinyurl.com/VPCafe

VPSD Technology
August 15 at 5:29 PM ·

The VPSD Tech team had a busy day today! In just 4 hours, we had around 250 student laptops picked up for the upcoming school year. We will be back from Noon to 4:00pm tomorrow, as well as afternoons/evenings on Monday and Tuesday for those who signed up. Remember: VPSD is going full 1:1 initiative for student laptops. These laptops are personalized for the induvidual student. If you have not signed up for a laptop, you can still sign up for Monday and Tuesday pickup times, using the link on the Infinite Campus Parent Portal!

post_text: Congratulations to the VPMS Sixth grade for a very successful and informative 4th Annual Festival of Nations. The Sixth grade students have been studying various countries around the world since August. Each student created projects on their countries to display to the entire Valley Park School District! After walking through all the displays, attendees were asked to leave comments for the Sixth graders about what they liked and learned about their countries. What a talented group of Sixth grade students we have at VPSD! #VPpride #GoHawks

post_text: The Valley Park School District will be dismissing school early on February 5, 2020 to ensure our students and staff arrive home safely. Registration for Valley Park Elementary School's 2020-2021 full-day, tuition-free kindergarten program begins Monday, February 10.

Registration Dates:
By Appointment Only
Monday, Feb 10 - 9AM-6PM
Tuesday, Feb 11 - 9AM-2PM
Wednesday, Feb 12 - 9AM-6PM
Thursday, Feb 13 - 9AM-2PM.

To find out more you can contact our Elementary School office at (636) 923-3600 or visit www.vp.k12.mo.us/kindergarten

At Valley Park School District, we develop leaders today in preparation for tomorrow. #VPpride #VPClassOf2033

post_text: Basketball season kicked off this week! If you are 60+ years old and live in the Valley Park School District, have children, grandchildren or relatives who attend VPSD you may obtain a FREE Golden Club Card. One of the many benefits includes free admission to VPSD sporting events! If you would like to join, please contact Jaime Gast at jgast@vp.k12.mo.us or (636) 923-3690. #VPGoldenClub #VPpride #GoHawks 🏀 🧡 💙 🦅

post_text: Today is GivingTuesday, a global generosity movement unleashing the power of people and organizations to transform their communities and the world. Join us and donate to the Valley Park Education Foundation. Scholarships from the VPEF go toward college scholarships for our VPHS students! Our goal today is to raise enough for one $500 scholarship! Let's see what a difference a day can make in the lives of our students. #VPpride #GoHawks
